.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-STATUS 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-status \- show session progress
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch status
[\fB\-\-porcelain\fR|\fB\-\-for\-prompt\fR[\fB=\fIFORMAT\fR]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B status
shows whether a session is active, which change is selected, and how many
hunks have been included, skipped, discarded, or remain.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-porcelain
Print machine-readable JSON. The JSON includes session state, selected change
details, file review details, progress counts, and skipped hunks.
.TP
.BI "\-\-for\-prompt" "[=" FORMAT "]"
Print a shell prompt segment only when a session is active. If
.I FORMAT
is omitted, print
.BR STAGING .
Format fields include
.BR {status} ,
.BR {progress_status} ,
.BR {iteration} ,
.BR {processed} ,
.BR {total} ,
.BR {included} ,
.BR {skipped} ,
.BR {discarded} ,
.BR {remaining} ,
.BR {selected_file} ,
.BR {selected_line} ,
.BR {selected_ids} ,
and
.BR {selected_kind} .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-start (1)
